# MCP Server Rules

## CONSTRAINTS

**CRITICAL**:
- Use MCP servers when available
- Prioritize MCP servers over standard tools

**MANDATORY**:
- Check tool availability before use
- Use standard tools as fallback (graceful degradation)

---

## Available MCP Servers

| Server | Purpose | Usage Guidelines |
|--------|---------|------------------|
| **Magic MCP** | React components, UI elements, 21st.dev patterns | React/UI component generation |
| **Context7** | Library documentation, API references, version-aware solutions | All code-related requests requiring library documentation |
| **Playwright** | Browser automation, screenshots, E2E testing | Frontend testing (mandatory), backend E2E testing |
| **Framelink Figma** | Figma files, components, layouts, icons | Design file access and component extraction |
| **Filesystem** | Bulk file ops, directory trees, pattern search | Extended file operations, bulk reading, metadata |
| **Obsidian** | Vault operations, wikilinks, frontmatter | Vault operations, see @obsidian-docs-rules.mdc for details |
| **GitHub** | GitHub platform interaction, repository management | Issues, PRs, branches, commits, releases, code search, repository operations |

## Fallback Patterns

| Primary | Fallback |
|---------|----------|
| Playwright MCP | Cursor Browser (`mcp_cursor-ide-browser_*`) |
| Obsidian MCP | Standard file tools with Obsidian-compatible formatting |
| Filesystem MCP | Standard file read/write tools |

